    "name": "Anacite Quantifier",
    "type": "alien",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Anacite quantif ers are the assessors of Aballon. They quantify the odds of success and try to determine all potential outcomes, constantly estimating potential risk, reward, and payof for myriad situations, from the viability of a new technology or policy to the f nancial success of stocks. Incredibly intelligent and quick thinkers, quantif ers perform advanced mathematical calculations and statistical analyses in fractions of a second. They use these calculations and assessments to determine potential outcomes in the physical world, digital spaces, cultural paradigms, and biological behavior.<br/> Quantif ers are similar in shape to a praying mantis, with an enlarged cranial cavity and four dexterous pincers. The majority of them work in governance, determining the potential outcomes of proposals and policies, but others guide planetary economics and investments or even serve as bookies."
        }
    ],
